    "latin-name": "Brassica rapa subsp. rapa",
    "plant-description": "Turnips are a root vegetable commonly grown in temperate climates worldwide for its white, bulbous taproot. Small, tender varieties are grown for human consumption, while larger varieties are grown as feed for livestock."
